CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 12, 1965, pg. 16, reads: "At Arts Festival - Numerous Pittsburgh Negro artists exhibited examples of their work and displayed their talents at the Pittsburgh Arts Festival, held in Gateway Center all of last week. ... in right photo, Muriel Wynn [Murrel] Jones (far right) of 3264 Camp St. stand in front of her exhibit and explains to an audience her five glass colages [collages] entitled 'Halleluia [Hallelujah],' 'Praise Him,' 'Out of This World,' 'Hi Stranger' and '...And Heaven Too.' Others exhibiting were Donald Paul Coleman, City Council stenotyper, of 218 Dunseith St.., who exhibited three paintings (enamels) entitled 'Wind Flowers,' 'Spring Forest' and 'The Waste Garden' and Stanley Waters Jr."
TitMainTitle: Murrel Wynn Jones talking to two women about her mosaics, in booth at Three Rivers Arts Festival, Gateway Center, Downtown
